-- в”Ђв”Ђ Ordway в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Ordway is a subscription billing and revenue automation platform that helps SaaS, usage-based, and fintech companies manage quote-to-cash, invoicing, and revenue recognition.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom (contact sales)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2018, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Washington, D.C., United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Ordway Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Ordway review: subscription billing and revenue recognition platform for SaaS companies. Quote-to-cash features, custom pricing, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Ordway (ordwaylabs.com) is a subscription billing and revenue automation platform that helps SaaS, usage-based, and fintech companies manage the full quote-to-cash cycle, from pricing and invoicing through revenue recognition and reporting. The company was founded in 2018 by Sameer Gulati, who serves as CEO and was previously one of Zuora's first product managers before becoming Chief Product Officer at Spree Commerce, which was acquired by First Data; that billing-industry background shaped Ordway's focus on the operational pain points, manual invoicing, spreadsheet-based revenue recognition, and disconnected CRM and finance systems, that mid-market SaaS finance teams face as they scale. Ordway is headquartered in Washington, D.C., and has raised institutional funding from investors including Rise of the Rest Seed Fund, Lerer Hippeau, Clocktower Technology Ventures, and CRV. The platform's core capabilities include flexible subscription and usage-based (metered) billing, automated invoicing and dunning, ASC 606 and IFRS 15 revenue recognition automation, CPQ-style quoting, multi-entity and multi-currency support, and reporting on SaaS metrics such as MRR and churn, all exposed through an API-first architecture designed to plug into existing CRM, ERP, and payment stacks such as Salesforce, NetSuite, and Stripe. Ordway targets mid-market SaaS, cloud, and fintech companies with complex or evolving pricing models, particularly those blending flat subscriptions with usage-based or transaction-based pricing, who have outgrown basic invoicing tools but are not yet ready for the cost and implementation overhead of enterprise platforms like Zuora. Pricing is not publicly listed and is quote-based, tailored to transaction volume, billing complexity, and company size. Ordway's main competitors in the subscription billing and revenue automation space include Zuora, Chargebee, Recurly, and BillingPlatform, with Ordway generally positioning itself as a more configurable, faster-to-implement alternative to legacy enterprise billing suites for growth-stage companies.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'cf66e303-0e7b-4d2e-b35e-ae3a7ac44901';

