-- в”Ђв”Ђ Orgvue в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Orgvue is an organizational design and workforce planning platform that lets HR and business leaders model, visualize, and simulate changes to org structure, headcount, and skills.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom (contact sales)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2005, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$201-500 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$London, United Kingdom$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Orgvue Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Orgvue review: organizational design and workforce planning software with scenario modeling and skills analysis. Features, pricing, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Orgvue (orgvue.com) is a cloud-based organizational design and workforce planning platform that lets HR, strategy, and business leaders import and harmonize workforce data, visualize org structures, and model scenarios for restructuring, mergers and acquisitions integration, and headcount planning. The company was founded in 2005 by Rupert Morrison and is headquartered in London, United Kingdom, having grown from an organizational consulting background into a dedicated software platform; it has raised a total of about 56.4 million dollars in funding, including investment from Morgan Stanley, and reports roughly 260 employees as of 2026. Orgvue's core differentiator versus generic business intelligence or spreadsheet-based org planning is that it is purpose-built around organizational and workforce data models: it connects to and cleans data from multiple HR and finance systems to build a trusted baseline, then lets users build interactive org charts and dashboards, run what-if scenario modeling to compare the cost and structural impact of alternative organizational designs in real time, and map skills and competency taxonomies to analyze workforce capability gaps against future demand. These capabilities make it especially useful for large-scale reorganizations, cost-reduction initiatives, and strategic workforce planning tied to skills and future-of-work analysis, rather than day-to-day HRIS record-keeping. Orgvue's target customers are HR, people analytics, and organizational design teams at large and mid-size enterprises undertaking complex restructuring, M&A integration, or long-range workforce planning, typically working alongside or on top of a core HCM system such as Workday or SAP SuccessFactors rather than replacing it. Pricing is not publicly disclosed and is sold through an enterprise, quote-based sales process. Orgvue competes with organizational design and workforce planning tools such as Visier and ChartHop, as well as the workforce planning modules within Workday and SAP SuccessFactors, differentiating itself through its dedicated focus on org modeling and skills-based scenario planning rather than being a module bolted onto a broader HCM suite.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '4cd26b5d-cf7d-49f1-82c5-0fb63f754a1f';

