-- в”Ђв”Ђ Ortto в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Ortto (formerly Autopilot) is a marketing automation and customer data platform that unifies customer data, multi-channel messaging, and analytics; it was acquired by Canva in April 2026.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$199/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2012, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Sydney, Australia$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Ortto Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Ortto review: customer data and marketing automation platform, now part of Canva. Pricing plans, key features, and top alternatives compared.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Ortto (ortto.com), formerly known as Autopilot, is a marketing automation and customer data platform that unifies customer data with multi-channel messaging, including email, SMS, push notifications, in-app messages, forms, and surveys, inside a single visual customer journey builder. The company was founded in 2012 in Bondi Beach, Australia, by brothers Michael, Chris, and Peter Sharkey, initially as Bislr before adopting the Autopilot name and product in 2015; the founders relocated the company back to Australia in 2018 to rebuild the platform, and in March 2022 it was rebranded from Autopilot to Ortto to reflect an expanded focus on unifying customer data, messaging, and analytics rather than automation alone. Ortto is headquartered in Sydney, Australia, with a US presence in San Francisco, and serves more than 11,000 customers across 190 countries, including Atlassian, Microsoft, and Patreon. Its core differentiator is combining customer data platform functionality, ingesting behavioral, transactional, and demographic data, directly with marketing automation and reporting in one product, reducing the need to stitch together separate CDP, email service provider, and analytics tools. Pricing is subscription-based and scales with contact volume: a Starter plan begins around 199 dollars per month for 5,000 contacts, Professional plans start around 509 dollars per month with annual billing for 10,000 contacts, a Business plan runs about 849 dollars per month annually with more advanced analytics, and Enterprise plans are custom-quoted, with a 14-day free trial available. Ortto's target users are marketing teams at SaaS, ecommerce, and high-tech companies that want behavior-triggered, multi-channel campaigns without hiring a dedicated marketing operations engineer. In a major strategic shift, Ortto was acquired by design platform Canva in April 2026 alongside AI workspace startup Simtheory, as Canva pushes beyond design tools into marketing automation and agentic AI infrastructure; financial terms were not disclosed. Ortto's principal competitors include HubSpot, ActiveCampaign, and Klaviyo, with Ortto typically differentiating on its unified customer-data-plus-automation architecture and multi-channel, not just email, messaging.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '6216dfaa-05dd-4223-a596-dbb3ee514d3c';

